I'm new to this topic, and I wouldn't recommend for anyone who's very new. The pace is too fast, and it seems like a robotic presentation instead of teaching someone.
This course is very specific to the software company and not on generic RPA notions

It gives you overlook of things to consider in very bureaucratic way. It's catch-all and a good resource to consider everything but very AAE specific. Solution itself doesn't sound great. Tests are mainly just word-to-word questions and don't test your comprehension of the issue at all.

I think this course would have benefitted from a short introduction to the Solution which it is set up to support. The explanations of the Discovery and Design Process were interesting albeit the strong focus on the Excel based AA documents felt like missing the opportunity to discuss the thoughtprocess.Long Quizzes for validating details things like sheet names felt old fashioned and left me the impression that I was just regurgitating most of what is presented in this course and forgetting it immediatly afterwards.
not so much. should have provided software to actually do it ourselves
Very Automation Anywhere specific. While it is useful to understand some basics, many of the detailed elements of the course would be difficult to implement independently.

RPA is a booming field accross the business verticals. The course gives us a good idea of RPA possibilities, benefits, discovery and design which would equip us to have insights that can help identify potential areas of work that can be automated using RPA. The course gives valuable insights in this respect and gives us a reasonable hands on experience of the pre-development phase of RPA. I'm sure the insights received would help in my work and career at large.
